content.problemStatement:
You have 222 counters aaa and bbb, both initialised as 000. You also have a score initialised as 000.

At the start of every minute from minute 111 to minute NNN, you **must** increase **either** aaa or bbb by 111.

Additionally, there are MMM events. The ithi^{th}ith event happens at minute Ti+0.5T_i+0.5Ti​+0.5 and has type CiC_iCi​ (Ci∈{1,2})(C_i \in \{1, 2\})(Ci​∈{1,2}).

At each event, the counters or the score is updated as:

`if (type == 1):
    if (a &gt; b):
        score = score + 1;
    else:
        a = 0;
        b = 0;
else:
    if (a &lt; b):
        score = score + 1;
    else:
        a = 0;
        b = 0;
`Your task is to **maximise** the score after NNN minutes have passed.


Input Format

The first line of input will contain a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases.
Each test case consists of multiple lines of input.

The first line of each test case contains two space-separated integers NNN and MMM — the number of minutes and the number of events.
The second line of each test case contains MMM integers T1,T2,…,TMT_1,T_2,\ldots,T_MT1​,T2​,…,TM​ — where the ithi^{th}ith event happens at minute Ti+0.5T_i + 0.5Ti​+0.5.
The third line of each test case contains MMM integers C1,C2,…,CMC_1,C_2,\ldots,C_MC1​,C2​,…,CM​ — the type of the ithi^{th}ith event.




Output Format
For each test case, output on a new line, the maximum score after NNN minutes have passed.
